Shares of several real estate companies are trading higher as markets gain on positive coronavirus outlook. Optimism surrounding the virus has led to hopes of an upcoming return to economic activity, which would benefit the sector.
Stocks That Hit 52-Week Highs On Thursday

Shares of several real estate companies and REITs are trading higher amid positive market sentiment on speculation that coronavirus cases in some hotspots could soon level off. A sooner recovery could benefit the economy and real estate sector.

Shares of several oil and energy companies are trading lower as oil prices continue to be pressured by oversupply as a result of output from Saudi Arabia and Russia, as well as weakening demand due to coronavirus disruption on the economy.
Equinix shares are trading lower. Several insiders from the company sold many of their shares in the company. The broader market is also trading lower amid the coronavirus spread.
